✅ SQL Q1: Find employees who earn more than their manager

Question:
Given the employee table:

| emp_id | ename | magr_id | sal |
|--------|-------|---------|-----|
| 1      | xyz   | 3       | 200 |
| 2      | pqr   | 3       | 600 |
| 3      | abc   | null    | 500 |
| 4      | efh   | 6       | 800 |
| 5      | uht   | 6       | 200 |
| 6      | iut   | null    | 500 |

Write a query to return the employees whose salary is greater than their manager.

Answer:
sql
SELECT e.ename, e.sal
FROM emp e
JOIN emp m ON e.magr_id = m.emp_id
WHERE e.sal > m.sal;


